Computational Techniques in Biomedical Engineering

This wiki page provides comprehensive details and step-by-step explanations of the Python code used in the project "Practice 1: Computational Techniques in Biomedicine".

The project contains four main computational exercises:

Circle Metrics Calculation
Time Conversion
Number Parity Determination
Leap Year Identification

1. Circle Metrics Calculation
This section of the code calculates the area and perimeter (circumference) of a circle given its radius.

The formulas used for these calculations are:

Area: π * r²
Perimeter (Circumference): 2 * π * r
