3. Number Parity Determination
This part of the code determines if a provided integer number is even or odd.
It is even if it is divisible by 2

4. Leap Year Identification
The last section identifies whether a given year is a leap year or not. A year is considered a leap year if it is divisible by 4, except for end-of-century years, which must be divisible by 400 to be leap years.


These exercises demonstrate basic computational techniques using Python, which is an essential skill for Biomedical Engineering. Remember, mastering these basics will be a stepping stone towards more complex computational problem-solving within the field of biomedicine.

Happy coding!
